<specimenCount box="[494,602,363,390]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" type="female">3 females</specimenCount>
measured). Body length 9.2–10.0 mm. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[1200,1282,363,390]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–10" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1060,1084]" captionTargetBox="[188,1401,191,1028]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[178,1410,181,1036]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 8–10. Trichotichnus spp., habitus. 8, T. fukuharai Habu, 1957 (Yunnan); 9, T. angustitarsis sp. n. (S Tengchong); 10, T. subrobustus sp. n. (holotype). Scale bar = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781687" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781687/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
. Morphological character states are as described for 
<emphasis box="[595,774,400,425]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
H. 
<taxonomicName authority="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase, 2022" authorityName="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase" authorityYear="2022" box="[629,774,400,425]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trichotichnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustitarsis" status="sp. n.">angustitarsis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[781,844,399,425]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[781,844,399,425]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but differing or limited as follows.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,150,1065]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Dorsal side of body black, shiny, very slightly iridescent on elytra; ventral side blackish brown. Base of mandibles and occasionally the very narrow lateral margins of pronotum reddish brown; palpi and antennae brownish yellow; legs brownish yellow or light brown, occasionally femora very slightly infuscate.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,150,1065]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
Head comparatively large (HWmax/PWmax 0.71–0.74, HWmin/PWmax 0.58– 0.62). Eyes smaller and less convex than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase, 2022" authorityName="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase" authorityYear="2022" box="[320,491,577,602]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trichotichnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustitarsis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[320,491,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">T. angustitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[497,559,576,602]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[497,559,576,602]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(HWmax/HWmin 1.17–1.27), in lateral view oval. Genae wider, about as wide as antennomere 1. Tempora longer (about 0.3–0.4 as long as eye diameter and more oblique. Fronto-clypeal suture more impressed and clypeus more convex. Supraorbital furrows slightly wider. Supraorbital setigerous pores situated slightly behind level of posterior margin of eye and removed from supraorbital furrows by distance wider than width of antennomere 1. Left mandible sharply bent approximately in the apical quarter, subtruncate at tip. Dorsal microsculpture highly obliterated, meshes on frons not recognizable. Antennae shorter, not reaching pronotal basal edge, with antennomeres 4–8 about 2.7–3.0 as long as wide. Basal antennomere about as long antennomere 3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,150,1065]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
Pronotum similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase, 2022" authorityName="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase" authorityYear="2022" box="[507,679,825,850]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trichotichnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustitarsis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[507,679,825,850]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">T. angustitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[685,748,825,851]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[685,748,825,851]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(PWmax/PL 1.50–1.58), also widest at the end of the anterior third, but more strongly narrowed basally (PWmax/PWmin 1.22–1.26), slightly more convex, more deeply emarginate apically and with apical angles more narrowly rounded. Microsculpture even more obliterated, meshes not recognizable medially on disc in some specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,150,1065]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Elytra relatively shorter (EL/EW 1.45–1.49, EL/PL 2.81–2.98; EW/PWmax 1.26–1.30), with less distinct humeral denticle, acuter sutural angle and narrower and more convex intervals apically; discal pore on interval 3 more distinct.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781711" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6781711" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781711/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" startId="16.[151,264,1947,1971]" targetBox="[157,1427,1097,1915]" targetPageId="16">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1947,2043]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,340,1947,1971]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">FIGURES 29–33.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase, 2022" authorityName="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase" authorityYear="2022" box="[346,613,1947,1971]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trichotichnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subrobustus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[346,613,1947,1971]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Trichotichnus subrobustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[619,675,1947,1971]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[619,675,1947,1971]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
29, terminal lamella of aedeagus; 30 &amp; 31, median lobe of aedeagus (holotype); 32, gonocoxite; 33, laterotergite, gonosubcoxite, and gonocoxite (N Dizhengdang). Dorsal (29 &amp; 31), lateral (30 &amp; 32) and ventral (33) views. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm (29, 32 &amp; 33), B = 1.0 mm (30 &amp; 31).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,151,609]" box="[199,915,151,177]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">
Metepisternum (
<figureCitation box="[384,465,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–22" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[176,1424,201,1937]" captionTargetId="figure-19@13.[162,1425,181,1939]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 18–22. Trichotichnus spp. (18–20, right male protarsus; 21 &amp; 22, left metepisternum). 18, T. fukuharai Habu, 1957; 19 &amp; 21, T. angustitarsis sp. n.; 20, T. hamulipenis sp. n.; 22, T. subrobustus sp. n. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781701/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) shorter, only slightly longer than wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Tarsi shorter; metatarsus slightly shorter than HWmin; metatarsomeres 1–4 comparatively sparsely setose ventrally. In male, pro- and mesotarsomeres 1–4 comparatively weakly widened, with tarsomeres 2 and 3 about as long as wide. In both sexes, mesotarsomere 1 shorter than mesotarsomeres 2 and 3 combined.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">
Median lobe of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[494,629,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–33" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1947,1971]" captionTargetBox="[157,1427,1097,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-415@16.[151,1436,1089,1923]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 29–33. Trichotichnus subrobustus sp. n. 29, terminal lamella of aedeagus; 30 &amp; 31, median lobe of aedeagus (holo- type); 32, gonocoxite; 33, laterotergite, gonosubcoxite, and gonocoxite (N Dizhengdang). Dorsal (29 &amp; 31), lateral (30 &amp; 32) and ventral (33) views. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm (29, 32 &amp; 33), B = 1.0 mm (30 &amp; 31)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781711" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781711/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Figs. 29–31</figureCitation>
) robust, with a small transverse apical capitulum, in lateral view arcuate on dorsal side; its ventral margin almost straight in middle portion and slightly convex before apex; ventral side edged laterally in apical part and very shallowly depressed between margins; terminal lamella (
<figureCitation box="[1238,1321,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–33" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1947,1971]" captionTargetBox="[157,1427,1097,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-415@16.[151,1436,1089,1923]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 29–33. Trichotichnus subrobustus sp. n. 29, terminal lamella of aedeagus; 30 &amp; 31, median lobe of aedeagus (holo- type); 32, gonocoxite; 33, laterotergite, gonosubcoxite, and gonocoxite (N Dizhengdang). Dorsal (29 &amp; 31), lateral (30 &amp; 32) and ventral (33) views. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm (29, 32 &amp; 33), B = 1.0 mm (30 &amp; 31)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781711" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781711/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) in dorsal view wide and short, much wider than long, concave, with sides roundly converging to very widely rounded apex. Apical orifice in dorsal position, wide apically. Internal sac with a small, angularly curved apical spine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[402,563,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–33" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1947,1971]" captionTargetBox="[157,1427,1097,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-415@16.[151,1436,1089,1923]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 29–33. Trichotichnus subrobustus sp. n. 29, terminal lamella of aedeagus; 30 &amp; 31, median lobe of aedeagus (holo- type); 32, gonocoxite; 33, laterotergite, gonosubcoxite, and gonocoxite (N Dizhengdang). Dorsal (29 &amp; 31), lateral (30 &amp; 32) and ventral (33) views. Scale bars: A = 0.5 mm (29, 32 &amp; 33), B = 1.0 mm (30 &amp; 31)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781711" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781711/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Figs. 32 &amp; 33</figureCitation>
): gonocoxite comparatively narrow and weakly curved in ventral view, about 0.7 times as long as gonosubcoxite, with moderately wide base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="319" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,547,573]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is a combination of the Latin prefix 
<emphasis box="[950,989,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">sub</emphasis>
- and the Latin adjective 
<emphasis box="[1266,1361,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">robustus</emphasis>
, referring to the rather robust body.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781713" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6781713" box="[151,762,1983,2007]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781713/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" startId="17.[151,250,1983,2007]" targetBox="[151,1434,634,1957]" targetPageId="17">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,762,1983,2007]" box="[151,762,1983,2007]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,288,1983,2007]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">FIGURE 34.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase, 2022" authorityName="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase" authorityYear="2022" box="[294,562,1983,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trichotichnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subrobustus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[294,562,1983,2007]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">Trichotichnus subrobustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[568,625,1983,2007]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[568,625,1983,2007]" pageId="17" pageNumber="318" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, distribution.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,354,150,176]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Comparison.</emphasis>
In combination of characters, including coloration, shape of pronotum, not sulcate protibia with three similar sized preapical spines on outer margin and one pair of marginal setae on last abdominal sternite of male, this new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase, 2022" authorityName="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase" authorityYear="2022" box="[554,727,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trichotichnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustitarsis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[554,727,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">T. angustitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[735,799,222,248]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[735,799,222,248]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but well differing from it in having body smaller, more robust, appendages shorter, head larger, genae wider, left mandible subtruncate at apex and metepisternum shorter. In the same characters and having one pair of marginal setae on last abdominal sternite of male, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase, 2022" authorityName="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase" authorityYear="2022" box="[1233,1395,294,320]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trichotichnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subrobustus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1233,1395,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">T. subrobustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="18" pageNumber="319" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
also differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Habu" authorityYear="1957" box="[372,508,330,356]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trichotichnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fukuharai">
<emphasis box="[372,508,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">T. fukuharai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which shares with the latter new species strongly obliterated dorsal microsculpture and rather narrow and markedly convex elytral intervals apically. Other distinctive characters of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase, 2022" authorityName="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase" authorityYear="2022" box="[1234,1395,366,392]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trichotichnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subrobustus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1234,1395,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">T. subrobustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="18" pageNumber="319" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are listed in the description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="319" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,438,464]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[362,447,438,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 34" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1983,2007]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,634,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-219@17.[151,1435,633,1960]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 34. Trichotichnus subrobustus sp. n., distribution." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6781713" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6781713/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
). Known from northwestern 
<collectingRegion box="[773,859,439,465]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[874,946,438,464]" name="China" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">China</collectingCountry>
), within Gongshan County, where it occurs at altitudes of 
<quantity box="[311,469,474,501]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.69" metricValueMax="1.88" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" unit="m" value="1690.0" valueMax="1880.0" valueMin="1500.0">1500–1880 m</quantity>
. This new species occurs sympatricly with 
<taxonomicName authority="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase, 2022" authorityName="Kataev &amp; Hongbin &amp; Wrase" authorityYear="2022" box="[953,1126,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trichotichnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustitarsis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[953,1126,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">T. angustitarsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1132,1196,474,500]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1132,1196,474,500]" pageId="18" pageNumber="319" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
